# UMS — University Management System Rules

## Stack
- Flutter + Firebase (Firestore + Auth) + Provider/Riverpod
- Language: Arabic RTL only
- Font: Cairo (mandatory on ALL text)
- Theme: Material 3 — Light + Dark

## AppColors Reference
- Primary:    #001835 (light) / #0B1524 (dark)
- Container:  #0F2D52 (light) / #152238 (dark)  
- Gold:       #FED65B
- Teal:       #00A694
- Surface:    #F7F9FB (light) / #0B1524 (dark)
- OnSurface:  #191C1E (light) / #E2E8F0 (dark)

## Hard Rules (NEVER break)
1. Zero hardcoded colors — always Theme.of(context).colorScheme
2. Zero mock data — always StreamBuilder/FutureBuilder from Firebase
3. Zero onPressed:null — every button must be wired
4. Zero stubs — complete implementation only
5. All padding/margin → start/end (not left/right)
6. All Text → overflow: TextOverflow.ellipsis inside cards

## Firestore Roles
- users/{uid}.role → "student" | "professor" | "admin"
- users/{uid}.status → "pending" | "active"
- Student pending = cannot login (show Arabic message)

## Cross-Portal Data Rules
- Attendance write → BOTH attendance/{courseId} AND attendance/{studentId}
- Grades write → BOTH grades/{courseId} AND grades/{studentId}  
- Announcements read filter: student=['all','student'] / prof=['all','professor']
- Requests collection is SHARED across all portals